	(text "External connections\n\nCheck out what else is in 1st gen mux\nDo we want reset on FTDI RTS?\nBe clear on 3.3V / 5V for FTDI interface; Every is 5V!\n\nFor +12V / +5V, use same scheme as on 1st gen mux?\ni.e. 78L05 OR switcher built-in on Every?\n\nExtra signal candidates:\n* External override for PIN_BIASes?\n* opposite polarity RTS\n* GNDD\n\nLocal decoupling."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 13.716 28.956 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "05c6c03b-6089-4b9a-9ad8-ec9a4607fc04")
	)
	(text "CONNECT ME\nSOMEWHERE \n(GNDA, GNDD)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 169.926 149.352 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "0ee6fc47-2a12-4bb6-aa60-7a5da5b71bb6")
	)
	(text "TBD\n\nPIN_BIAS through op amp? NO, since it can/should be overridden by \nPIN diode current switched, and can be high-Z\n\nGNDD connects where? Arduino?? Tied to GNDA here?\nThinking this is ONLY a trace on the mux boards... it's all GNDA here?\n\nTHERMSEL lines: put on D6-D8?\n\nHow much to spread out DSUB-37's?"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 74.422 24.384 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "c65ee347-1fe4-40a0-b37f-f5522d29c960")
	)
	(text "NEW REV\n\nUse Pins D6, D7, D8, D13 for IV_ON1, 2, 3, 4"
